race.comment: The well-related CAVALRY MAN (8) (half to G2 winner Positive Peace) is a consistent conveyance who has hit the top-five in all eight starts this time in work. Gets some weight relief with the 2kg claim and should get a cosy run in transit from gate two. Ticks a few boxes for a race like this. VICTORY FLAME (9) has a solid record at this circuit with two wins and a second from just four starts. Must be respected from the Archibald barn. MANNERHEIM (11) was too bad to be true at the latest effort but go on the strong Doomben win prior. Worth another chance. LUDOVISI (6) won two starts ago then back to earth last time when fourth over 1600m at Doomben. Look for an improved run.
